		<description><![CDATA[One Firefox feature that I am in love with is that doodad in the top right corner that lets you search different sites like Google and Amazon from any page at any time. It&#8217;s the search box and it has been a real time-saver for me. When Firefox 2 came out, developers were given the [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span class="leadin">One <a href="http://mozilla.com/firefox/">Firefox</a> feature that I am in love with is that doodad in the top right corner that lets you search different sites like Google and <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2F&amp;tag=shifpixe0b-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325">Amazon</a> from any page at any time.</span> It&#8217;s the search box and it has been a real time-saver for me.</p>
<p>When Firefox 2 came out, developers were given the ability to augment their search plugins with suggestions as you type. Out of all the search engines I use from my search box, the top two are definitely Google and Amazon. While Google quickly took advantage of this new feature, Amazon did not.</p>
<p>Because I use Amazon so often, I decided to write my own search plugin for Amazon that will give you search suggestions as you type. Hopefully you will find it useful as well. And, as a bonus, if you use it and buy anything from Amazon, you will automatically help support Shifting Pixel.</p>
<h3>Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>Firefox 2+</li>
<li>IE7 (suggestions are not supported by IE7)</li>
</ul>
<h3>To install</h3>
<div class="left half">
<h4>Firefox 2+</h4>
<ol>
<li>Remove the default Amazon.com search engine from Firefox.
<ol>
<li>Click on the search engine selection icon in the top right corner (most likely a Google icon).</li>
<li>Click on &#8220;Manage Search Engines&#8230;&#8221;</li>
<li>In the Search Engine Manager, click on &#8220;Amazon.com&#8221; and click the &#8220;Remove&#8221; button.</li>
<li>Click &#8220;OK.&#8221;</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>Add my Amazon.com search engine with suggestions.
<ol>
<li>Click on the search engine selection icon in the top right corner.</li>
<li>Click on &#8220;Add Amazon.&#8221;</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="right half">
<h4>Internet Explorer 7</h4>
<ol>
<li>Click on the search engine selection icon in the top right corner.</li>
<li>Under &#8220;Add Search Providers&#8221; click on &#8220;Amazon.&#8221;</li>
<li>A box will pop up asking you to confirm. Click &#8220;Add Provider.&#8221;</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="clearer">&nbsp;</div>
